reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Definitely worth the purchase.
reviews.reviewText: This desk is perfect for small or large spaces. We have moved it to a few different areas and looks good in all of them. (We just like to move stuff a lot) It was also not extremely heavy, but sturdy and the outlets are in the perfect spot. Just wish there were a couple more. Had to take it apart once because of user error, but otherwise it was easy to put together. I would just suggest paying attention to the specifics of the instructions.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Working space and lots of it!
reviews.reviewText: I got the 53in and I'm very pleased. I have put many pieces of furniture together in fact everything in my home from bookshelves, dressers, assorted tables and crafting carts to computer desks and this was so easy. I did need help with some of the assembly as the instructions stated it was easier with 2 people when aligning the two desktop pieces and attaching the upper shelf. I am very pleased it's light enough for 2 people to move and sturdy enough to hold some weight.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 9, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good build prob won’t last long term
reviews.reviewText: I got the smaller of the 2 desks. It was vary easy to build and was relatival sturdy.made out of particle board and solid metal. little shorter than expected but I haven’t necessarily looked at the height before buying. Had extra screws and hardware and really clear instructions for both left and right angle set up…had some minor dents in the wood one right at the front that I could easily rotate to the back but I had already screwed on so not doing that unless it keeps annoying me .was also missing a bag of screws #11 or 1 possibly misplaced them in the mess of plastic protectant but they are not critical to the structure only used to anchor the headphone hooks.great cheap option for an L desk with pretty good finish by cheap I mean less then 300$. Drawers are disappointing similar to pop up fabric baskets with a facing on them prob won’t last long term.led works and the adjustable foot grips are nice. Good in between for minimalist design and need for storage was able to get in the desk. I do like that the side storage could be taken off and used separately in theory like if I didn’t need a desk anymore I would prob keep the side section as a stand.

reviews.reviewText: Exactly (well, almost exaclty- I'd have to make my own for exactly what I want 😂) what I needed.
